@Jose Faeti perfect.
The story behind the game is magnificent. I have a PDF of Perfect Works, it's simply amazing.
That's sad that Xenosaga it's not made by Square, the game lost everything in this continuation.

@lurkingfriend

They focused too much on it being an open world and it doesn't have the strong feeling of Xenogears, also found Xenogears characters design one of the greatests of all time, Xenoblade turned out like most other "generic" JRPG, but Xenosaga was still great. Luckily we've had JRPG masterpieces on every generation, you just need to look for them. But there's a lot of myth about these not being good anymore just because one of the bigger franchises went to shit, and the reason was really simple. But If I have to say, more than the JRPG in general, which as I said, there's plenty of modern masterpieces, I miss a type of JRPG I've never ever seen again, the big, epic type ones, full of great characters and incredible music, such as FFIX. 

How can it be I haven't seen bigger and livier cities in platforms such as PS4 if this was made on PS1? And the story kept getting bigger while little and amazing sub stories develop each time you visited a place, now everything is going from A to B with stupid and forgettable side quests in the middle. Sakaguchi talent was in fact story telling, but I can't believe there isn't any other genious like him in the japanese video game industry who has his warm touch to make an epic story.

