A game TELLS you it's awesome if it's price at the game store is STILL 60 bucks after 3 years.  Too bad the greatest hits came out for it, the value would be MUCH higher than it is now. (Up side is more people had gotten to play this masterpiece of a game.)

The soundtrack is my favorite soundtrack ever for game music. (Hell, even more than most movie scores, sans Hans Zimmer's works.)
